
Nmap (Network Mapper)

1. Overview
Nmap is a powerful open-source network scanning and enumeration tool used to identify hosts, open ports, running services, operating systems, and potential vulnerabilities.

Useful in:
- Bug Bounty reconnaissance  
- Pentesting (network mapping)  
- Asset discovery in large environments  

----

2. Key Features
- Host discovery  
- Port scanning (TCP/UDP)  
- Service version detection  
- OS fingerprinting  
- Script automation via NSE (Nmap Scripting Engine)  
- Firewall & IDS evasion techniques  

---

3. Installation

Linux (Debian/Ubuntu)
sudo apt install nmap

Arch Linux
sudo pacman -S nmap

macOS
brew install nmap

Windows
https://nmap.org/download.html

---

4. Common Commands ! 

nmap <target>
nmap -sV <target>
nmap -A <target>
nmap -p 1-65535 <target>
nmap -Pn <target>
nmap -sC -sV <target>

----
5. Important Parameters

Flag	        Description

-sS	          SYN stealth scan
-sV	          Detect service version
-O	          OS detection
-A	          Aggressive scan (OS + version + scripts)
-Pn	          Skip host discovery
-p-	          Scan all ports

--script vuln	Run vulnerability scripts
--top-ports 100	Fast top-ports scan
--reason	Show why a port is detected as open/closed
--open	Show only open ports



6. Advanced Use Cases

Firewall Evasion
nmap -f -sS <target>

Using NSE Scripts
nmap --script http-title <target>

Mass Scan + Output
nmap -sC -sV -oN result.txt <target>


